South Korea names new military chief . South Korea announced a replacement on Thursday for its top military commander whose two - year term expires this year . Kim Dong - jin , chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff , will be replaced by Yoon Young - nam , currently Chief of Staff of the Republic of Korea army . Yoon will be succeeded by Do Il - kyu , presently commander of the Third Republic of Korea Army . A defence ministry statement did not say when the new appointments would take effect . South Korea ' s military has come under heavy criticism for failing to detect a North Korean submarine that intruded into southern waters last month . Of 26 North Koreans who landed from the vessel , 22 have been killed , prompting threats of " merciless retaliation " by Pyongyang . 
